# üìò Source Code Management & Git ‚Äì Complete Notes

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Source Code Management (SCM)

Source Code Management (SCM) is a system used to:

- Store source code
- Track changes
- Manage versions
- Enable teamwork
- Restore old files

It helps developers work safely and efficiently.

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ What is Git?

Git is a Distributed Version Control System (DVCS).

## Full Form of Git
Git has no official full form.
(Unofficial: Global Information Tracker)

## Created By
Git was created by Linus Torvalds in 2005.

## Features
- Fast
- Secure
- Offline support
- Branching
- Free & Open Source

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ File System

A File System stores files and folders on a computer.

Example:
C:/Users/file.txt  
/home/user/file.txt

It does NOT track changes.

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Version Control System (VCS)

A Version Control System tracks file changes over time.

It allows:
- History tracking
- Team collaboration
- Backup
- Restore
- Conflict management

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Difference: File System vs VCS

| Feature | File System | VCS |
|---------|-------------|-----|
| History | No | Yes |
| Backup | No | Yes |
| Teamwork | No | Yes |
| Tracking | No | Yes |
| Restore | No | Yes |

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ Types of VCS

1. Local VCS (RCS)
2. Centralized VCS (SVN)
3. Distributed VCS (Git)

Git is most popular.

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ Git Stages

Git has three stages:

1. Working Directory
2. Staging Area
3. Repository

Flow:
Working ‚Üí Staging ‚Üí Repository

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ Git Workflow

Edit ‚Üí Add ‚Üí Commit ‚Üí Push

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ Important Git Commands

## Setup
git --version  
git config --global user.name "Name"  
git config --global user.email "email@gmail.com"

## Initialize
git init

## Status
git status

## Add
git add file.txt  
git add .

## Commit
git commit -m "message"

## History
git log  
git log --oneline

## Branch
git branch  
git branch dev  
git checkout dev  
git checkout -b feature1

## Merge
git merge branch

## Pull
git pull

## Push
git push origin main

## Clone
git clone URL

## Remote
git remote -v  
git remote add origin URL

## Reset
git reset --soft HEAD~1  
git reset --hard HEAD~1

## Stash
git stash  
git stash pop

## Diff
git diff

---

# üîü Connect Local to GitHub (HTTPS)

## Steps

1. Create repo on GitHub
2. Initialize Git
   git init
3. Add files
   git add .
   git commit -m "first commit"
4. Add remote
   git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
5. Push
   git push -u origin main

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Connect Using SSH

SSH = Secure Shell

## Step 1: Generate Key
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "email@gmail.com"

Press Enter 3 times.

## Step 2: Start Agent
eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"  
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa

## Step 3: Copy Key
cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

## Step 4: Add to GitHub
GitHub ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí SSH ‚Üí New Key ‚Üí Paste

## Step 5: Test
ssh -T git@github.com

## Step 6: Add SSH Remote
git remote add origin git@github.com:user/repo.git  
git push -u origin main

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ .gitignore

.gitignore tells Git which files to ignore.

Example:

node_modules/  
.env  
*.log  
*.exe  

These files are not tracked.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ Branching Strategies (Companies)

## Git Flow
main  
develop  
feature/*  
release/*  
hotfix/*  

Used in big projects.

## Feature Branch
feature-login  
feature-payment  

## Trunk Based
Only main branch

Used by Google, Meta

## Release Branch
For stable versions

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ Types of Branches

## Main / Master
Production branch

main

## Development
Integration branch

develop

## Feature
New feature work

feature-login

## Hotfix
Emergency fixes

hotfix-1.0.1

## Release
Before deployment

release-v1.0

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ Environments

## Development
For coding

## Staging
Testing before live

## Production
Live system

Flow:
Dev ‚Üí Staging ‚Üí Production

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ Hotfix Branch

Used for urgent bug fixes.

Flow:
main ‚Üí hotfix ‚Üí main + develop

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ Feature Branch

Used for one task.

Example:
git checkout -b feature-payment

After work ‚Üí merge

---

